com.ptc.core.foundation.lifecycle.server.impl

Class LifeCycleTemplateConstraintFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ptc.core.meta.type.runtime.server.impl.AbstractModelBasedConstraintFactory
      • com.ptc.core.foundation.lifecycle.server.impl.LifeCycleTemplateConstraintFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OperationIdentifierConstants, ConstraintClassNameConstants, java.io.Serializable, NetFactor

    public final class LifeCycleTemplateConstraintFactory
extends AbstractModelBasedConstraintFactory
implements java.io.Serializable
    Attribute specific constraint factory. If the attributes represented by the logical identifiers "lifecycle" or "lifecycle.id" are in the passed in AttributeTypeIdentifier array then constraints will be added. The following constraints are added based on the passed in OperationIdentifier (operation/constraints): search - SUGGESTED_VALUES_CONSTRAINT create - SUGGESTED_VALUES_CONSTRAINT update - IMMUTABLE_CONSTRAINT

    Use the newLifeCycleTemplateConstraintFactory static factory method(s), not the LifeCycleTemplateConstraintFactory constructor, to construct instances of this class. Instances must be constructed using the static factory(s), in order to ensure proper initialization of the instance.



    Supported API: true

    Extendable: false
